 :tx/provenance :observed
 :tx/rationale "LIVESTORE ARCHITECTURE PROPOSAL (Session 039): The fundamental insight: DiskLayout and Store are separate objects that don't know about each other. write_tx() is a filesystem operation with no concept of current store state — it writes a file and deletes the cache because that's the only safe thing a filesystem layer can do. The fix is not better cache invalidation but ELIMINATING THE SEPARATION between the store and its persistence layer. DESIGN: LiveStore struct owns both DiskLayout and Store. LiveStore::open(path) deserializes store.bin once (300ms). LiveStore::store() returns &Store (0ms). LiveStore::write_tx(&mut self, tx) does three things atomically: (1) write EDN txn file to disk for durability, (2) apply transaction to in-memory Store via transact(), (3) serialize updated Store to store.bin via write_index_cache. This makes the cache ALWAYS fresh because every write updates it. No invalidation, no rebuild, no stale data — by construction. WHAT DIES: invalidate_cache(), fitness.json, coherence.json, analytics.json, incremental rebuild path, slow rebuild path, fingerprint validation, meta.json. ~400 lines of cache management code becomes self.layout.write_index_cache(&self.store). WHAT THIS ENABLES: (1) The daemon (PERF-4) becomes trivial — a LiveStore that doesn't exit. CLI mode and daemon mode share the same LiveStore, same write-through semantics, same persistence guarantees. The only difference is process lifetime. (2) Sub-second braid status (~500ms: 300ms deserialize + 50ms coherence + 50ms routing + 100ms write-through). (3) Correct-by-construction caching — impossible to serve stale data. CRASH SAFETY: The append-only guarantee (C1) makes this bulletproof. If the process crashes between 'update in-memory' and 'write store.bin', the txn file is already on disk — the next LiveStore::open() picks it up via the incremental path. No data loss, no corruption, no inconsistency. PERFORMANCE MODEL: LiveStore::open() 300ms (bincode, once per process). live.store() 0ms (pointer deref). live.write_tx() ~100ms (txn file + bincode serialize). Total braid status: ~500ms. From 97s to 0.5s = 194x improvement from start of session."
